<l>iruticai puṇari ṉēyiṭai varumē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>If the word <foreign xml:lang="ta">uṇṭu</foreign> denotes existence, the disappearance of the pre-</l>
<l>ceding final [vowel] with [its] consonant, and the change into the</l>
<l>sound <foreign xml:lang="ta">ḷ</foreign> of the preceding consonant - these two alterations may</l>
<l>occur when a plosive occurs as initial of the following word.<note place="foot">Eg. <foreign xml:lang="ta">uṇṭu + poruḷ &gt; uḷporuḷ | uṇṭuporuḷ.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
